Package entity

Class Filter

java.lang.Object
entity.Filter
public class Filter extends Object
Provides utility methods for filtering BTO projects based on criteria such as flat availability and neighborhood.

    • filterByAvailableFlats

      public static List<Project> filterByAvailableFlats(List<Project> projects, FlatType type, int minAvailable)
      Filters the given list of projects to only include those with a minimum number of available flats of the specified type.
      Parameters:
      projects - The list of projects to filter.
      type - The type of flat (e.g., 2-room or 3-room).
      minAvailable - The minimum number of available flats required.
      Returns:
      A list of projects that meet the availability criteria.

    • filterByNeighborhood

      public static List<Project> filterByNeighborhood(List<Project> projects, String neighborhood)
      Filters the given list of projects to only include those located in the specified neighborhood.
      Parameters:
      projects - The list of projects to filter.
      neighborhood - The neighborhood name to match (case-insensitive).
      Returns:
      A list of projects located in the specified neighborhood.

    • filterProjects

      public static List<Project> filterProjects(List<Project> projects, int filterChoice, int minAvailable, String neighborhood, FlatType type)
      Filters the given list of projects based on a selected filter criteria.
      Parameters:
      projects - The list of projects to filter.
      filterChoice - The filter criteria to apply (1, 2, or 3).
      minAvailable - The minimum number of available flats (used for choices 1 and 2).
      neighborhood - The neighborhood to match (used for choice 3).
      type - The type of flat to check (used for choices 1 and 2).
      Returns:
      A filtered list of projects based on the selected criteria.
